@component server-core
@intent HTTP + WS upgrade core sub-module of the Constellation live-board `server` family (v1.1 split per phase_2 2026-06-04, parent manifest `server.eux` carries cross-cluster operational directives). Owns: (a) HTTP request surface — `/api/state` (no-store snapshot), `/api/events` (SSE pushed on `fs.watchFile` 500ms with 20s `: ping` keep-alive), `/api/feedback` (POST ≤ 32MB body, data-URL attachments extracted to `feedback-atts/` per §13.11 rule 5 storage discipline), `/join/<group>?key=` (dynamic collab onboarding md gated by `wsKeyRole`), and `INTEGRATION_DOCS` whitelist (public protocol SSoT + reference client + 3 representative `.eux` + BREW.md only; private agreements absent by construction). (b) WS upgrade handshake — non-`/ws` rejection, key-query→meta translation (collab/upstream key role), the canonical inbound 3-frame sequence (`SERVER_HELLO` bare → `CUSTOM/AgentList` value-nested → `CUSTOM/History` if non-empty). (c) Per-connection role classification reducer (axis 1 of `@machine` — ANON / BOARD / AGENT / ANON_PROBE). (d) Boot bind policy — **v2.4.11 secure-by-default**: listen binds loopback (`127.0.0.1`) unless `WS_BIND` env explicitly opts into network exposure; rationale = board (dashboard) connections are an unauthenticated trusted-operator surface (key issue/list + SetMain reachable without credentials), so non-loopback exposure must be a deliberate operator decision, surfaced via startup warning. The envelope convention (CUSTOM-wrapped application messages vs bare transport framing) is canonically anchored here. (Re-distilled from reference @ v2.5.87, 2026-06-12 — v2.4.7 WS_PRIMARY_AGENT-unset startup warning + v2.4.11 secure-by-default bind absorbed.)
@expansion temperature=0.2 model=agent/claude template=estreux/v0.1
@targets vanilla
@profile backend-service
@source constellation/reference/runtime/server.cjs(247-277 wsCollabOnboardMd · L267-300 wsHandleOrch dispatch) · constellation/reference/runtime/server.cjs(WS upgrade + SERVER_HELLO/AgentList/History sequence · listen-block boot bind + startup warnings) · WS-PROTOCOL §13.11 attachment storage + §13.16.4 HELLO/flap discipline
@state
  MAX_BODY      : number = 33554432   # 32MB cap for POST /api/feedback body (over → req.destroy)
  HIST_CAP      : number = 200        # per-channel stored-event cap (referenced; ring lives in server-history)
  sseClients    : Set<res>            # open SSE subscribers (state pushes)
  wsConns       : Set<conn>           # all live WS connections (agents + boards)
@ports
  in   PORT                     : number = 7878        # env.PORT
  in   WS_BIND                  : string = '127.0.0.1' # env.WS_BIND — listen interface; loopback default (v2.4.11 secure-by-default); network exposure = explicit opt-in (e.g. 0.0.0.0 / specific interface IP), token gate recommended alongside
  in   LIVE_BOARD_WS_TOKEN      : string?              # optional token gate (enforced in ws-core upgrade)
  out  GET  /api/state          : current state.json (no-store)
  out  GET  /api/events         : SSE; emits `state` on connect + on every state.json change (fs.watchFile 500ms); 20s `: ping`
  out  POST /api/feedback       : append entry → feedback.jsonl (≤32MB); data-URL atts → feedback-atts/ (path ref kept inline)
  out  GET  /join/<group>?key=  : dynamic onboarding md (key+host embedded; collab → 403 if wsKeyRole(key)!='collab')
  out  GET  <whitelist docs>    : INTEGRATION_DOCS only — protocol SSoT + onboarding doc + reference client + 3 representative .eux (ws-conn-bar · ws-tool-card · ws-collab-invite) + BREW.md
  out  static PUBLIC/            : path-jailed to PUBLIC (`../` escape → 403)
  out  /ws upgrade              : ws-core.handleUpgrade → conn; query key (?key/?upstreamKey/?collabKey) sets collab/upstream meta
@deps
  http      : node http server
  fs        : state read + watchFile + feedback IO + (history IO delegated to server-history)
  ws-core   : deps-0 WS framing (handleUpgrade, event())
  -relay    : constellation/server-relay.eux (post-HELLO routing + A2A relay receives classified conn)
  -history  : constellation/server-history.eux (History frame at upgrade; record() at relay-time)
  -keys     : constellation/server-keys.eux (wsKeyRole lookup for joinCollab + WS upgrade meta)
@wire
  envelope:
    convention: CUSTOM-wrapped {type:CUSTOM, name, value, ...} for application messages
    bare_transport: [SERVER_HELLO, HELLO, Heartbeat, PersistentAdapterSmoke]
    canonical_builder: wscore.event(type, payload)     # NEVER construct {type:...} literals for application messages
    mixing_failure_mode: silent dashboard drop ("connected" but channels stay empty — real downstream-adoption pitfall)
  upgrade_sequence_3_frames:
    1: SERVER_HELLO{protocolVersion:'0.3'}              # bare top-level transport framing
    2: CUSTOM/AgentList/value:{main, agents, serverTime}# role first, so monitors classify A2A correctly
    3: CUSTOM/History/value:{events, cold, archived}    # ONLY if non-empty (active + cold/archived stubs); fully delegated to -history
@behavior
  bootBind         : listen on (PORT, WS_BIND) — loopback unless WS_BIND opted in (loopback = 127.0.0.1 / ::1 / localhost); startup log includes effective bind; non-loopback → ⚠⚠ startup warning (board connections are unauthenticated — anyone on the network can issue/list keys + SetMain; use trusted network only or front with reverse-proxy + auth; exposure is deliberate opt-in)
  bootWarnPrimary  : startup logs effective main agentId (env WS_PRIMARY_AGENT — state owned by -relay); if left at generic default → ⚠ startup warning that any main session with a different agentId classifies as local (main-role demotion); remedy = inject WS_PRIMARY_AGENT on (re)start, or SetMain handoff at runtime
  broadcastState   : on state.json change (fs.watchFile 500ms) → write `event: state` to every sseClient (newlines flattened)
  serveFeedback    : POST body (≤MAX_BODY 32MB, destroy if over); JSON parse (400 on bad); stamp receivedAt; map atts via storeAtt; append feedback.jsonl
  storeAtt         : if att.src is data-URL → decode (base64/uri) to feedback-atts/<ts-rand.ext>, replace src with {stored:path, bytes, mime}; code/text bodies stay inline (§13.11 rule 5 hybrid mode)
  joinCollab       : /join/<group>?key= → wsKeyRole(key)=='collab' (from -keys) else 403 md; else wsCollabOnboardMd(host, key) — connect line + IDE/CLI vs autonomous-runtime branch + paste-ready onboarding prompt
  integrationDocs  : serve only whitelisted files; anything else 404 (private agreements deliberately absent — see derive doc_safety)
  onUpgrade        : reject non-/ws (socket.destroy); ws-core.handleUpgrade → conn; read key from query → wsKeyRole (from -keys) → set conn.meta.collab/upstream; add to wsConns; emit 3-frame sequence
  onClose          : delete conn from wsConns; if agent-of-record → wsAgents.delete (delegated to -relay) + wsPushAgentList
@machine connection_role
  # reducer: (connRole, event) → connRole — axis 1 of original two-axis @machine
  initial: ANON
  states:
    ANON:
      entry: SERVER_HELLO + AgentList + History-if-nonempty; key meta set → collab/upstream
      on:
        HELLO_with_agentId → AGENT      # entry: register agentId, replace prior conn, push AgentList (delegated to -relay)
        HELLO_without_agentId → ANON_PROBE   # security gate per §13.16.4 unauthorized-probe class
        no_HELLO → BOARD                  # board/user — its inbound routes to agents (via -relay)
    BOARD:
      on:
        HELLO_with_agentId → AGENT
        close → ⊗
    AGENT:
      on:
        close → ⊗                          # entry: if agent-of-record → wsAgents.delete + push AgentList
    ANON_PROBE:
      entry:
        - conn.meta.anonymous = true
        - log {remoteAddr, ua, raw HELLO}   # origin observability
        - NO wsAgents.set; NO wsPushAgentList; relay path drops anything from this conn (-relay anonymous gate)
@invariants
  # P3 AST 계약스키마 — phase_3 2nd cut per eux-format v1.2 §2.6 (EstreUX edd2fb7 — 4 sub-section state/temporal/transaction/causality + 17 vocabulary keyword).
  state:
    - sseClients + wsConns membership: ordered (add on connect, remove on close); 동시에 multiple conn 가능 (bounded by OS limits)
    - INTEGRATION_DOCS whitelist: bounded membership (whitelist-only docs — private agreements unreachable by construction)
    - PUBLIC static: path-jailed to PUBLIC ('../' escape 금지) — bounded path traversal
    - WS conn meta (collab/upstream): monotonic per conn lifetime (key meta set on upgrade, never changes thereafter)
    - bind interface (WS_BIND): fixed per process lifetime (resolved once at boot; loopback default — non-loopback only via explicit env opt-in)
    - connection_role state member-of {ANON, BOARD, AGENT, ANON_PROBE} — exclusive membership
  temporal:
    - SSE keep-alive: 20s after each ping interval (`: ping` heartbeat)
    - fs.watchFile cadence: 500ms after state.json mtime change (broadcastState trigger)
    - POST /api/feedback body: ≤ MAX_BODY (32MB) within single request lifetime (over → destroy + 413)
    - WS upgrade 3-frame sequence: SERVER_HELLO first, then AgentList, then History (if nonempty) — within upgrade transaction (ordering)
    - storeAtt data-URL decode: at-most-once per attachment (file write 1회, src replace 1회 — idempotent)
  transaction:
    - onUpgrade 3-frame sequence: SERVER_HELLO → AgentList → History commit-then 진행 (이전 frame 완료 후 다음 frame emit)
    - serveFeedback: body parse → stamp receivedAt → storeAtt → append feedback.jsonl atomic (실패 시 partial commit 없음, rollback-safe)
    - storeAtt: data-URL decode → temp file → rename atomic (partial write 시 rollback-safe — feedback-atts/ dir state 보존)
    - register (delegated to -relay): wsAgents.set persist-before wsPushAgentList broadcast (commit-then 패턴)
    - boot: HTTP server bind (PORT, WS_BIND) + WS upgrade handler 등록 dual-write atomic (한쪽 실패 시 전체 abort)
  causality:
    - HELLO with agentId iff conn → AGENT post-register (register state transition)
    - HELLO without agentId iff conn → ANON_PROBE (anonymous_probe_gate — security against unauthenticated LAN probe)
    - no HELLO precedes BOARD classification (default board role for non-HELLO conn)
    - INTEGRATION_DOCS whitelist 외 path implies 404 (private agreements unreachable by construction)
    - envelope mismatch (bare framing for application msg) implies silent dashboard drop (mixing_failure_mode)
    - non-loopback bind implies startup ⚠⚠ warning emitted (secure-by-default — unauthenticated board surface exposure requires operator awareness)
    - main agentId left at generic default implies startup ⚠ warning emitted (main-role demotion guard — env omission on restart is the observed failure mode)
@metamorphic
  # P4 property/metamorphic 후보 — phase_3 2nd cut per eux-format v1.2 §2.7 (EstreUX edd2fb7).
  round_trip:
    - state.json change → SSE broadcast → client state re-fetch: 동일 state.json snapshot (broadcast round-trip)
    - storeAtt: data-URL → decode → temp file → src replace → read back: bytes identical for code/text bodies (att roundtrip)
    - wscore.event(type, payload) → emit → server receive: envelope structure preserved (canonical builder roundtrip)
  idempotency:
    - integrationDocs: 동일 whitelisted path 의 GET 결과 deterministic + idempotent (file content stable)
    - joinCollab: 동일 key 의 wsKeyRole(key) lookup 결과 동일 (wsKeys 변경 없으면 idempotent)
    - broadcastState: 동일 state.json snapshot 의 SSE event payload 동일 (idempotent broadcast)
  determinism:
    - wscore.event(type, payload): 동일 input → 동일 envelope bytes (canonical builder deterministic)
    - upgrade sequence: 동일 query key + history state → 동일 3-frame output sequence
    - storeAtt path generation: 동일 ts + rand seed → 동일 feedback-atts/ 경로 deterministic (단 rand seed 가 process-local)
@operation_discipline
  derive:
    envelope_convention: application MUST emit as CUSTOM/<name>/value{...} (3-field shape); transport framing (SERVER_HELLO/HELLO/Heartbeat/PersistentAdapterSmoke) stays bare. Stored events preserve full envelope including source-stamped timestamp; replay never clobbers. Mismatch = silent dashboard drop.
    doc_safety: INTEGRATION_DOCS is an explicit whitelist; private agreements unreachable by construction
    anonymous_probe_gate: HELLO without agentId is held at transport layer but never registered (security against unauthenticated LAN probe → phantom channel accumulation incident, real ~100 synthetic channels observed)
    secure_by_default_bind: board connections carry no credential gate (trusted-operator model) — so network reachability, not connection auth, is the effective security boundary. Default loopback bind closes the remote unauthenticated key-management / SetMain / agentId-spoof vectors in one move; WS_BIND exposure is deliberate opt-in, warned at boot, with reverse-proxy + auth (or at least the token gate) advised in front
